// useExportDiagram
// Exports a rendered Mermaid diagram SVG element as a downloadable SVG or PNG file.

PNG export draws the SVG to an off-screen canvas at 2x retina resolution.
Computed styles are inlined into SVG clones before export so the output is self-contained.
canExport reflects whether an SVG element is currently present in the container.

FUNCTION useExportDiagram() -> { svgContainerRef, exportAsSVG, exportAsPNG, canExport }  EXPORT
  Manages state: canExport.
  svgContainerRef is a callback ref that updates canExport when the container mounts/unmounts.

---

FUNCTION svgContainerRef(node)
  Stores the container reference. Sets canExport to false if node is null, or to whether
  an SVG child element exists if node is provided.

---

FUNCTION exportAsSVG(filename)
  Finds the SVG in the container, clones it, inlines all computed styles, serializes to XML,
  and triggers a browser download as {filename}.svg.

---

FUNCTION exportAsPNG(filename)
  Finds the SVG, determines its dimensions (falling back to 800x600 if getBBox fails),
  clones and inlines styles, serializes to a data URL, and draws it onto a 2x-scaled canvas.
  Converts the canvas to a PNG blob and triggers a browser download as {filename}.png.
  Resolves (never rejects) — times out after 10 seconds if the image fails to load.

---

FUNCTION inlineStyles(element)
  Recursively copies computed CSS styles onto each element's inline style attribute,
  ensuring exported SVGs render correctly outside the page context.

---

FUNCTION downloadFile(url, filename)
  Creates a temporary anchor element, sets its href and download attributes, clicks it
  programmatically to trigger the browser download, then removes the element.
